ty of personnel administrative areas and also in the U S  Military Postal Service  His assignments included Andrews Air Force Base  Maryland and Clark Air Base  Phillipines  He joined the Virginia Army National Guard in December 1987 and retired from the Reserve Component on 1 August 2005 at the rank of Master Sergeant after serving a total of over 24 1 2 years  Mr  Campbell joined the Virginia Military Institute s Army ROTC Program in March 1997 where he serves as a Human Resources Assistant  Personal Mr  Campbell has one son  Joshua  and they reside in Lexington  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 